body:
I've submitted https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/pull/3153, which should now behave the same way as key bindings.

If you're using mouse mode, this will require additional bindings though. Something like this probably:

```yml
mouse_bindings:
  - { mouse: Middle, action: PasteSelection, mode: ~mouse }
  - { mouse: Middle, mods: Shift, action: PasteSelection, mode: mouse }
  - { mouse: Middle, mods: Alt, action: Paste, mode: ~mouse }
  - { mouse: Middle, mods: Shift|Alt, action: Paste, mode: mouse }
```

If you do not add these additional bindings, you'll be able to paste even when in mouse mode, which is likely not desirable.

> ```yaml
> mouse_bindings:
>   - { mouse: Middle, action: PasteSelection, mode: ~mouse }
>   - { mouse: Middle, mods: Shift, action: PasteSelection, mode: mouse }
>   - { mouse: Middle, mods: Alt, action: Paste, mode: ~mouse }
>   - { mouse: Middle, mods: Shift|Alt, action: Paste, mode: mouse }
> ```

For some reason I don't see changes for adding new modes [here](https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/pull/3153/files#diff-477049f60a4e0056df655eec516628e7R794). It is also weird to have `{ mouse: Middle, mode: ~mouse}`. It reads as "if middle mouse button pressed not on mouse" :)

Why not follow same schema currently used for `AppCursor`? I.e. it indeed refers to exposing mouse actions to application.
